reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: With so many home project on slate, these zip ties prove both quality and versatile.We've used them to tighten and strap down fencing to posts and for cable management both indoors and outdoors.We've use them for balancing weighted objects, too and they've shown quite the durability.Where these stand out is cable management in my custom-made PC, wiring behind TVs and gaming consoles as those unruly tangled webs of cable turn into a streamlined bundle that's easier to maintain or move behind other objects.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A great value on zip ties
reviews.reviewText: Review of Black zip Ties 8 inch (1000 pack), 40 lbs tensile strengthIt’s always nice to have extra zip ties around so when I saw this 1000-pack, I ordered it. When I opened the package and pulled one out, I connected it and tried to pull it apart. I was surprised when it broke (I’m not that strong…). The listing claims 40lb tensile strength so I decided to do a simple test. I hung a 25lb bag of flour from a screw and put the zip tie to work. To be honest, I expected the tie to break, but I’m happy to report it handled the 25lb weight well (photos). I would not classify these zip ties as “heavy duty” as the listing claims. Still, for regular or light-duty use, they are a great value.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars NOT heavy duty
reviews.reviewText: I like the quantity, and they work well for what they are intended for. However, to advertise these as heavy duty is beyond a stretch. These are in no way, shape, or form heavy duty. I could break them by hand pretty easily. These are low grade zip ties at best. They have many uses, but if you really need something heavy duty, look elsewhere. I don't believe the 40lb strength claim for a second.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a set of 1,000 zip ties. They are 8" long and UV resistant. I always try to get UV resistant ties because they are rated for outdoor use and tend to last longer than non-UV cable ties. I use a lot of zip ties and a pack of 1000 is very helpful and cost effective.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Well-Made and Work Well for Numerous Projects and Tasks, Can't Beat the Quantity!
reviews.reviewText: My husband is glad to have this huge bag of 1000 Zipties because he is constantly needing them for "this or that" and in the past has had to go hunting for some, until now! He currently is using several to hold up and organize wiring on his side-by-side, and also to organize electrical cords in his garage. With this amount, he says he'll most likely never run out of them, and when in the middle of a project, that certainly offers peace of mind!
